# ks-eye v3: AI-Human Collaborative Research Assistant

**Step-by-step guided research. AI suggests. You decide. Nothing is fully automated.**

---

## Philosophy

ks-eye v3 is **NOT** an automated research tool. It is a **research assistant** that guides you through each step of the research process. At every stage, the AI drafts content and **waits for your review and approval** before moving forward.

| What the AI Does | What You Do |
|-----------------|-------------|
| Asks guiding questions | Define your topic and objectives |
| Drafts a research proposal | Review, edit, approve, or reject |
| Generates a JSON questionnaire | Review questions, add/remove, approve |
| Analyzes pasted data | Collect data offline, paste it in |
| Finds academic sources | Select which sources to include |
| Writes report sections | Approve or edit each section |
| Compiles final report | Choose output format, save |

---

## Quick Start

### Install

```bash
# Prerequisite: tgpt
go install github.com/aikooo/tgpt/v2@latest

# Install ks-eye
cd ks_eye
pip install -e .

# Optional: Word document output
pip install -e ".[docx]"
```

### Run

```bash
kseye        # Launches interactive step-by-step workflow
```

That's it. The tool will guide you through everything.

---

## The 8-Step Workflow

When you run `kseye`, it walks you through:

### Step 1: Define Your Topic
```
AI: "What is your research topic? What are your objectives?
     Who is your target population? What is the scope?"

You: Type your answers (multi-line, one per line)
     Press Enter on empty line to finish.
```

### Step 2: Review Research Proposal
```
AI: Drafts a complete proposal (Introduction, Problem Statement,
    Research Questions, Objectives, Significance, Methodology, Timeline)

You: Read it. Then choose:
  • "approve"           → move to next step
  • "edit: add more about X"  → AI revises
  • "regenerate"        → fresh draft
```

### Step 3: Design Questionnaire
```
AI: Generates a JSON questionnaire with:
    • Demographics section
    • 15-25 questions (multiple choice, Likert scales, open-ended, etc.)
    • Proper structure ready for survey tools

You: Review the JSON. Then choose:
  • "approve"           → JSON exported for your use
  • "edit: add 3 questions about satisfaction"  → AI modifies
  • "regenerate"        → new questionnaire
```

### Step 4: Collect Data (Offline)
```
AI: "Use this questionnaire to create your survey.
     Distribute it. Collect responses. Format as JSON.
     Then paste the data here."

You: (Do this offline — Google Forms, SurveyMonkey, paper, etc.)
     Come back and paste your collected JSON data.
     Or type "skip" if no data collection needed.
```

### Step 5: Analyze Data
```
AI: Analyzes your pasted JSON data:
    • Response count, demographics
    • Key findings per research objective
    • Statistical summaries (percentages, patterns)
    • Qualitative insights from open-ended responses
    • Limitations and recommendations

You: Review the analysis. Choose:
  • "approve"           → findings accepted
  • "reanalyze: focus more on demographic differences"  → AI re-analyzes
```

### Step 6: Literature Review
```
AI: Searches academic sources (Google Scholar, Semantic Scholar,
    CrossRef, arXiv, PubMed, SSRN, Wikipedia, etc.)
    Presents found sources as a numbered list.

You: Select which sources to include:
  • "select: 1,3,5,7"   → specific sources
  • "select: all"        → all sources
  • "skip"               → no literature review

AI: Synthesizes ONLY your selected sources into a literature review.

You: Review. Approve or request edits.
```

### Step 7: Write Report (Section by Section)
```
AI: Drafts each section one at a time:
    1. Executive Summary
    2. Introduction
    3. Literature Review
    4. Methodology
    5. Findings and Results
    6. Discussion
    7. Recommendations
    8. Conclusion

For EACH section:
You: Read it. Choose:
  • "approve"           → section finalized
  • "edit: make it more specific to..."  → AI revises
  • "skip"              → section excluded
```

### Step 8: Export Final Report
```
AI: Compiles all APPROVED sections into a final report with:
    • Cover page
    • Table of contents
    • All approved sections
    • References

You: Choose output format:
  • .txt  → Formatted text file (default)
  • .docx → Word document (if python-docx installed)

AI: Saves report + saves session for later resumption.
```

