---

## Questionnaire JSON Format

The questionnaire uses this structure:

```json
{
  "title": "Research Questionnaire",
  "description": "Instructions for respondents",
  "sections": [
    {
      "section_name": "Demographics",
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "Q1",
          "type": "demographic",
          "text": "What is your age?",
          "options": ["14", "15", "16", "17", "18"],
          "required": true
        },
        {
          "id": "Q5",
          "type": "likert_scale",
          "text": "Mobile learning improves my understanding",
          "options": ["Strongly Disagree", "Disagree", "Neutral", "Agree", "Strongly Agree"],
          "required": true
        },
        {
          "id": "Q10",
          "type": "open_ended",
          "text": "What challenges do you face with mobile learning?",
          "required": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Question types: `multiple_choice`, `likert_scale`, `yes_no`, `open_ended`, `ranking`, `matrix`, `demographic`

---

## Collected Data Format

When you paste your collected data, use this structure:

```json
{
  "responses": [
    {
      "respondent_id": "R001",
      "demographics": {
        "age": "16",
        "gender": "Female"
      },
      "answers": {
        "Q1": "16",
        "Q5": "Agree",
        "Q10": "Limited internet access at home"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## Commands

```bash
kseye              # Interactive step-by-step workflow (main use)
kseye version      # Show version
```

That's intentionally minimal. The tool is designed to be used interactively, not via flags.

---

## Output

### Text (.txt) — Default
Formatted research paper with:
- Cover page with topic and date
- Table of contents
- All human-approved sections
- Professional formatting

### Word (.docx) — Optional
Professional Word document with styled headings, tables, and sections.

### Session (.json) — Auto-saved
Full session state saved automatically for later resumption.

---

## AI Providers

Configure which AI provider each agent uses:

```bash
kseye              # Interactive → manage providers from menu
```

Available: `sky` (free), `phind` (free), `gemini`, `openai`, `groq`, `deepseek`, `ollama` (local), `kimi` (free), `isou` (free), `pollinations` (free)

---

## Architecture

```
ks_eye/
├── engines/
│   ├── research_assistant.py  ← Core: 8-step workflow engine
│   ├── tgpt_engine.py         ← AI provider integration
│   ├── scholar_search.py      ← Academic source search (10 types)
│   └── docx_formatter.py      ← Word document output
├── cli.py                     ← Interactive step-by-step CLI
├── config.py                  ← Settings + session management
├── ui.py                      ← Clean display components
└── data/
    ├── research_history/      ← Sessions and reports
    └── config/
        ├── settings.json
        └── agent_providers.json
```

